<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="399" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Field</persName>,
                                    Assistant Attorney-General, to <gloss type="to">United States
                                        marshal, New Haven, Connecticut</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-07-01"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 1, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">United States
                                    Marshal</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">New Haven,
                                Connecticut:</hi></p>
                            <p>The schooners Fancy and Winona are at Milford, alleged to have
                                violated the neutrality laws. See district attorney, and take care
                                of them and the men found on board.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>W. A. FIELD.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>